---
/**
 * GitHub Culture Callout Component
 * 
 * Displays a callout linking to posts about GitHub's culture.
 * This replaces the Jekyll {% include_cached github-culture.html %} tag.
 */
---

<div class="alert alert-primary text-center" role="alert">
  Interested in learning more about how GitHub works and what it's like to be a GitHubber?<br />
  <a href="/2021/02/01/what-to-read-before-starting-or-interviewing-at-github/" class="alert-link">
    Check out these popular posts on GitHub's culture and communication patterns
  </a>.
</div>

<style>
  .alert {
    position: relative;
    padding: 1rem 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    border: 1px solid transparent;
    border-radius: 0.375rem;
  }
  
  .alert-primary {
    color: var(--bs-primary-text-emphasis, #084298);
    background-color: var(--bs-primary-bg-subtle, #cfe2ff);
    border-color: var(--bs-primary-border-subtle, #b6d4fe);
  }
  
  .text-center {
    text-align: center !important;
  }
  
  .alert-link {
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--bs-primary-text-emphasis, #06357a);
    text-decoration: underline;
  }
  
  .alert-link:hover {
    color: var(--bs-primary-text-emphasis, #06357a);
    opacity: 0.85;
  }
</style>
